      "message": "Not for this CL, but I\u0027d really like to revisit how we structure String vs StringFragment. Ideally, it should be transparent/simple to create StringFragments from Strings (since this is \"free\"), and creating Strings from StringFragments should be explicit (since this is \"heavyweight\"). This is how things work with std::string and std/absl::string_view. We seem to have ours set up the other way around, though; we have an implicit String constructor that takes StringFragments, but nothing going in the opposite direction, and these operators turn \"StringFragment + StringFragment --\u003e String\" magically. This makes the expensive thing easy and the cheap thing hard.",
